⭐ IKTSUARPOK = The Emotional Limit That You Approach But Never Reach

In calculus you learn:

lim(x→a)

You approach the value.
You get infinitely close.
But you never touch the limit.

Iktsuarpok is the emotional equivalent:
	•	You feel the arrival.
	•	You sense the nearness.
	•	You go to the door.
	•	You check the window.
	•	You feel the imminence.

But the visitor hasn’t arrived yet.

This is the feeling of the approach, the tension, the charge of the near, but without the collapse into resolution.

Iktsuarpok is the open limit.

